verif_result.fix_hint:
Deterministic synthesis preflight rejected the RTL before Vivado.
Violated rule(s): activation_memory_exceeds_vivado_variable_bit_limit.
Functional simulation may pass, but this structural shape is known to cause pathological Vivado runtime/RSS.
Repair the indicted storage organization; do not change the public interface or functional behavior.
Violations:
- [activation_memory_exceeds_vivado_variable_bit_limit] Memory 'line_buf' is a single unpacked reg variable totalling 1204224 bits (depth=784, inner=1, element_width_bits=1536). Vivado rejects any single variable above 900000 bits (hard limit ~1,048,576 with [Synth 8-4556]). Bank the memory into multiple smaller variables, each well under the cap. Recommended: 13 bank(s) of depth 64 (bits_per_bank=98304). Sketch:
  reg [1535:0] line_buf_b0 [0:63];
  reg [1535:0] line_buf_b1 [0:63];
  reg [1535:0] line_buf_b2 [0:63];
  reg [1535:0] line_buf_b3 [0:63];
  reg [1535:0] line_buf_b4 [0:63];
  reg [1535:0] line_buf_b5 [0:63];
  reg [1535:0] line_buf_b6 [0:63];
  reg [1535:0] line_buf_b7 [0:63];
  reg [1535:0] line_buf_b8 [0:63];
  reg [1535:0] line_buf_b9 [0:63];
  reg [1535:0] line_buf_b10 [0:63];
  reg [1535:0] line_buf_b11 [0:63];
  reg [1535:0] line_buf_b12 [0:63];
  bank_idx = pixel_index / 64;
  bank_addr = pixel_index % 64;
Do NOT collapse the buffer further than the layer's logical pixel count; each bank just holds a contiguous slice.

